## `total_bytes(conn, inode) -> int`
<!-- checksum: blobs-6 -->

### Purpose
Test-introspection hook. Sum of all `length(data)` for the inode. Diverges from `stat.size` when holes exist.

### Implementation Notes

```python
def total_bytes(conn, inode):
    (n,) = conn.execute(
        "SELECT COALESCE(SUM(length(data)), 0) FROM blobs WHERE inode = ?",
        (inode,),
    ).fetchone()
    return n
```

### Test Strategy
- Used by the hypothesis stateful test in `test_durability`.

